Hello Nicolas,

Bjarne Andersen&#39;s suggestion, or some other non-heritrix solution may or 
may not be more appropriate for what you&#39;re trying to do, I don&#39;t know, 
but to answer your questions about heritrix...

You can pretty much accomplish what you describe by setting maxHops=0 on 
the TooManyHopsDecideRule, and by removing the TransclusionDecideRule. 
With those changes heritrix won&#39;t crawl beyond the seeds (and redirects 
from seeds, which are also treated as seeds by default).

If you want to do only the dns part of your task, you don&#39;t have to 
change the default settings at all, you can simply have a list of dns 
urls as seeds, e.g. dns:www.example.org. (The dns failures will take a 
while to get through the retry cycle, so if you want quicker results on 
the failures you might want to reduce the retryDelaySeconds and 
maxRetries settings on the frontier.)

Noah

